The paper deals with the problem of universal variable-to-fixed length coding of parametric sources, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The proposed coding scheme involves the use of a dictionary, which is a common technique in machine learning and natural language processing (cs.LG). The quantized type class of a sequence is based on partitioning the space of minimal sufficient statistics into cuboids, which is a concept from computational statistics (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the asymptotics of the coding rate, which is a topic in statistical inference (cs.SI). Finally, the paper provides a converse showing that the proposed rate is optimal up to the third-order term, which is a result in computational complexity theory (cs.CC).
